To say that the Yao Yao Ramen at Suzume is delicious is an understatement. As a self-professed Ramen snob, I was eager to taste the dish which has received such high praise in other reviews. It is the best Ramen I have eaten in NY, and one of my top 3 Ramen pics of all time (which includes my 2 month tour in Tokyo searching for the perfect bowl of Ramen). When prepared properly, Ramen transforms from a simple broth with noodles and vegetables into an almost religious experience. Chef Joshua skillfully produced the latter. Each bite simultaneously stimulated my senses and soothed my soul. The thoughtfullness and care that he puts into choosing his ingredients is evident. They play with each other exquisitely, and by the end of the meal caused what I can only describe as an out of body experience of bliss. The restaurant itself is cozy and intimate with a great vibe, lovely staff, yummy cocktails, and is 100% worth the wait (they do not currently take reservations and justifiably get quite busy on weekends). The menu is not limited to just Ramen, and every dish we tried has been as pleasing to the eye and palette as the Ramen.

Currently favorite Japanese restaurant - selective menu with a lot of special dishes. Note that this place is cash only.  First of all, beautiful and cozy little spot. Really friendly staff.  Cocktails - try the Chi Chi, Gigganjuice and Ami Tai.  The Spam Musubi is my favorite - a unique mix of flavors, with the saltyness and crispiness from the spam, touch of sourness from the pineapple bits, and the warmth and sweetness from the rice.  The Hawaiian fried chicken rice also surprises - crispy strips of fried chicken, Mac and cheese (yeah you read that right), greens, all atop a ride base. It's really good.  My other favorite is the salmon ramen. Salmon is fresh, slightly crispy on the outside, soft and sweet on the inside. Each bite is so satisfying; pair it with the ramen completes the experience.  The appetizer sushi, wings, fish tacos are great too.
